‘This could happen anywhere to anyone, unfortunately it happened to our victim,’ said Johnna Watson.

By Wednesday morning backers at raised more than $8,300 towards their $18,000 goal to pay for the teenager's treatment at St. Francis Memorial Hospital in San Francisco, according to Kron4 News.

The incident happened  when the victim was asleep in the rear of an Alameda-Contra Costa Transit bus in Oakland, shortly after 5 p.m on Monday.

Fleischman woke up with his clothing was on fire and tried to put it out himself.

Other passengers came to his aid but he suffered severe burns to his legs.

Once the bus driver realized what happened, he stopped the bus and called for assistance but the suspect fled the scene before police arrived.

The Helping Sasha Have a Speedy Recovery fund is aiming to raise over $20,000 dollars for the teenager.

